519
00:27:23,141 --> 00:27:24,142
a…

520
00:27:27,112 --> 00:27:29,914
I was relieved that he seemed to be doing well.

521
00:27:32,917 --> 00:27:35,353
I was worried because I saw it on the news.

522
00:27:35,420 --> 00:27:37,655
It's been a long time since I've been vulnerable to being hit.

523
00:27:41,960 --> 00:27:45,697
I'm glad you're doing well too.

524
00:27:48,066 --> 00:27:50,969
I'm sure she was completely disappointed with my old lady.

525
00:27:51,469 --> 00:27:53,471
Come eat again if you feel like it.

526
00:27:53,538 --> 00:27:54,539
(Customer 1) Mama added beer

527
00:27:54,606 --> 00:27:55,907
Ah yes

528
00:27:58,977 --> 00:28:01,413
Matilda, do you remember?

529
00:28:02,847 --> 00:28:06,084
Why did you disappear?

530
00:28:08,186 --> 00:28:10,555
Some strange past was discovered and he was expelled.

531
00:28:10,622 --> 00:28:12,824
Some people are saying things I don't understand

532
00:28:14,526 --> 00:28:18,163
(Akari) Adult video or mistress bank?

533
00:28:18,696 --> 00:28:20,598
Is that true?

534
00:28:20,665 --> 00:28:24,335
I'm sure she was the big sister you all looked up to.

535
00:28:24,969 --> 00:28:27,338
Girls really hated it

536
00:28:28,773 --> 00:28:31,409
It was so long ago, why now?

537
00:28:32,777 --> 00:28:35,680
Oh... bones came out from where the swamp was.

538
00:28:36,881 --> 00:28:38,550
(Yuta) In my memory

539
00:28:38,616 --> 00:28:41,686
I think you called Matilda once.

540
00:28:42,487 --> 00:28:45,256
Matilda said she would settle things with you...

541
00:28:45,323 --> 00:28:48,660
Maybe my memory is wrong though

542
00:28:49,728 --> 00:28:51,096
Ha…

543
00:28:51,162 --> 00:28:53,998
Did I kill Matilda?

544
00:28:55,200 --> 00:28:56,501
(Customer 2) Have you had beer yet?

545
00:28:56,568 --> 00:28:58,770
Oh, wait a minute...

546
00:29:00,605 --> 00:29:02,340
Why would I do that?

547
00:29:02,407 --> 00:29:05,510
You hated Matilda, you took Yun away.

548
00:29:06,077 --> 00:29:09,481
I took on the role of Minmei out of rivalry with Matilda.

549
00:29:09,547 --> 00:29:12,550
Besides, jealousy among girls sometimes goes out of control.

550
00:29:12,617 --> 00:29:14,619
 (Kisuke) Chen... - (Hajime) I guess that's a possibility... - (Akari) You're a middle school student, right?

551
00:29:14,686 --> 00:29:17,055
(Yuta) There was a high school student you dated, right?

552
00:29:17,122 --> 00:29:18,356
rode a bike

553
00:29:18,923 --> 00:29:21,126
You can't do it, but if he...

554
00:29:21,192 --> 00:29:23,962
(Customer 3) Mom, let me have a beer.

555
00:29:24,028 --> 00:29:26,698
What's left if you take the love from your aunt?

556
00:29:26,765 --> 00:29:28,433
(Customer 1) They treat me like a woman.

557
00:29:28,500 --> 00:29:32,203
(Customer 2) We really like the loose meat of old women.

558
00:29:33,471 --> 00:29:36,274
Don't worry! That's rude

559
00:29:36,341 --> 00:29:37,442
(Customer 1) What are you?

560
00:29:37,509 --> 00:29:38,343
(Customer 3) Don't disturb me.

561
00:29:38,409 --> 00:29:40,345
(Customer 2) There's no reason for you to say something like that!

562
00:29:40,411 --> 00:29:41,246
Get out!

563
00:29:42,914 --> 00:29:44,749
(noise)

564
00:29:48,286 --> 00:29:49,254
- (Hakuba) Hey! -(Hajime) What are you doing...

565
00:29:49,320 --> 00:29:50,755
(Hajime) Let go!

566
00:29:53,091 --> 00:29:54,759
(Sound of hitting the bowl)

567
00:29:54,826 --> 00:29:56,027
Stop it!

568
00:30:00,598 --> 00:30:02,033
Apologize!

569
00:30:03,034 --> 00:30:05,770
Yes, apologize to her!

570
00:30:12,977 --> 00:30:14,078
It's you!

571
00:30:15,146 --> 00:30:17,415
Please apologize to my precious regular customers!

572
00:30:22,453 --> 00:30:25,957
Hi... I'm sorry.

573
00:30:26,024 --> 00:30:28,927
-(Hajime) Sorry, sorry... -(Kisuke) Sorry...

574
00:30:28,993 --> 00:30:31,362
(Akuri) Excuse me, are you hurt? (Customer 3) Mom, what is this?

575
00:30:31,429 --> 00:30:32,964
Your bill is fine today, so please come again! (Customer 1) Okay, let's go.

576
00:30:32,964 --> 00:30:34,499
Today's bill is fine, so please come again! (Customer 3) Will you come again?

577
00:30:34,499 --> 00:30:34,899
Today's bill is fine, so please come again!

578
00:30:34,966 --> 00:30:38,136
Sorry, please come again!

579
00:30:38,770 --> 00:30:39,938
Sorry...

580
00:30:49,447 --> 00:30:51,049
(Akari) Yoisho

581
00:30:53,685 --> 00:30:54,686
(Yuta) Sorry.

582
00:30:56,154 --> 00:30:59,857
I can't stand it when you make fun of me...

583
00:31:03,194 --> 00:31:05,864
The economy was good back then.

584
00:31:05,930 --> 00:31:06,764
Huh...

585
00:31:06,831 --> 00:31:12,270
I was shown a lot of the bubble life that adults dream of.

586
00:31:12,971 --> 00:31:15,707
By the time I entered society, I was completely blown away.

587
00:31:17,475 --> 00:31:19,544
I wanted to go to apparel, but I can't.

588
00:31:19,611 --> 00:31:23,248
Still, I managed to get into the car business.

589
00:31:23,314 --> 00:31:24,749
Because I looked good

590
00:31:24,816 --> 00:31:25,817
Huh...

591
00:31:26,451 --> 00:31:30,521
My job is to serve tea, entertain, and laugh at sexual harassment.

592
00:31:30,588 --> 00:31:35,393
To guys who are smarter than me and can't even do the job.

593
00:31:35,894 --> 00:31:38,730
I was once told clearly that I was in the “mistress category.”

594
00:31:39,597 --> 00:31:43,768
Even that job was taken over by a younger person after I turned 30.

595
00:31:44,469 --> 00:31:46,771
That's why I opened my own store

596
00:31:47,372 --> 00:31:50,909
While paying off the debt left by my scumbag ex-husband.

597
00:31:50,975 --> 00:31:52,744
raise my daughter

598
00:31:52,810 --> 00:31:56,381
I earn money by selling okonomiyaki every day.

599
00:31:57,482 --> 00:31:59,984
There's nothing wrong with people saying things like that.

600
00:32:01,486 --> 00:32:04,722
Everyone works hard every day

601
00:32:05,523 --> 00:32:08,092
The ground is crawling and alive

602
00:32:09,594 --> 00:32:11,829
So do those drunk people.

603
00:32:13,097 --> 00:32:18,102
My boyfriend who was riding a motorcycle is also working hard in the transportation industry.

604
00:32:19,637 --> 00:32:21,973
Some say that their middle school years were the peak of their lives.

605
00:32:22,040 --> 00:32:23,508
There are a lot of them

606
00:32:24,075 --> 00:32:28,146
Hold a class reunion and dress up as much as you can

607
00:32:28,212 --> 00:32:31,549
She said she was just looking forward to talking about her memories of those days.

608
00:32:32,951 --> 00:32:36,587
I know it's only going to get harder from now on.

609
00:32:36,654 --> 00:32:40,425
Still, everyone walks on their own without complaining.

610
00:32:41,759 --> 00:32:44,329
To the elite who have lived a winning life like you.

611
00:32:44,395 --> 00:32:45,997
I want you to pity me

612
00:32:46,531 --> 00:32:48,333
I'm most angry

613
00:32:49,968 --> 00:32:50,969
Don't be conceited

614
00:32:53,037 --> 00:32:54,405
Thank you for your help

615
00:33:00,011 --> 00:33:03,748
Ha... I'm done too.

616
00:33:05,583 --> 00:33:09,087
I was sent to a remote area within the group.

617
00:33:09,153 --> 00:33:10,888
I'm told not to do anything

618
00:33:12,457 --> 00:33:16,661
My wife and daughter told me not to do anything...

619
00:33:17,462 --> 00:33:18,496
Huh...

620
00:33:19,497 --> 00:33:21,232
There is no longer any value in existence

621
00:33:22,633 --> 00:33:27,305
Even if you fight for years in court and are lucky enough to win.

622
00:33:27,372 --> 00:33:28,873
How old am I?

623
00:33:30,541 --> 00:33:35,480
In my former workplace and in my former life,

624
00:33:35,980 --> 00:33:37,248
can't go back

625
00:33:37,815 --> 00:33:38,816
Me too...

626
00:33:40,985 --> 00:33:41,853
It's finished

627
00:33:51,729 --> 00:33:54,332
(Akuri) The one who summoned Matilda was...

628
00:33:58,803 --> 00:34:01,873
I wanted to apologize to Matilda.

629
00:34:03,808 --> 00:34:06,377
I spread rumors

630
00:34:06,444 --> 00:34:10,415
Adult videos and mistress banks

631
00:34:12,617 --> 00:34:15,119
Yes, you were taken

632
00:34:16,120 --> 00:34:17,855
I was jealous of that person

633
00:34:18,790 --> 00:34:21,859
I confessed my truth and apologized.

634
00:34:29,467 --> 00:34:32,303
(Akari) You came, Matilda.

635
00:34:33,304 --> 00:34:36,574
I have to settle things with you, Minmei.

636
00:34:37,875 --> 00:34:39,277
(Akari) That person...

637
00:34:40,077 --> 00:34:41,646
I knew everything

638
00:34:43,014 --> 00:34:44,816
It's fine

639
00:34:44,882 --> 00:34:48,052
It would be cool to have a past as punk as that.

640
00:34:49,520 --> 00:34:52,857
(Akari) Isn't there a problem in the staff room?

641
00:34:53,991 --> 00:34:57,161
Everyone is laughing, I just want you to believe me a little more

642
00:35:00,431 --> 00:35:01,365
It's true

643
00:35:02,467 --> 00:35:05,736
Actually, I'm not good enough to be a school teacher.

644
00:35:08,773 --> 00:35:12,243
More than that, you'll be filming Minmei's scene tomorrow, right?

645
00:35:12,743 --> 00:35:15,713
But being kidnapped by bad guys is also old-fashioned.

646
00:35:15,780 --> 00:35:18,382
I think Minmei should fight a little too.

647
00:35:18,449 --> 00:35:19,650
Like Shihomi Etsuko

648
00:35:20,384 --> 00:35:21,486
Give it a try

649
00:35:23,187 --> 00:35:24,889
Ha ha ha

650
00:35:26,757 --> 00:35:30,161
(Undispersed) Even if it's a sword, then what?

651
00:35:30,895 --> 00:35:31,863
-(Missan) Ho-(Akari) Uff

652
00:35:31,929 --> 00:35:33,531
- (Misan) And... - (Misan/Akuri) Ho!

653
00:35:33,598 --> 00:35:35,299
(Unsold) Well, let's try it one more time.

654
00:35:36,400 --> 00:35:38,135
- (Akari) - (Misan) to flick

655
00:35:40,371 --> 00:35:41,272
passing each other

656
00:35:41,339 --> 00:35:44,842
We pass each other and touch each other's arms

657
00:35:47,512 --> 00:35:50,615
Did you say, “I’m not good enough to be a teacher”?

658
00:35:51,382 --> 00:35:54,051
I don't know what it means though

659
00:35:54,118 --> 00:35:56,354
A lot of things happened in the past, right?

660
00:35:57,822 --> 00:35:59,624
And one more thing

661
00:36:00,925 --> 00:36:04,328
I accepted the role of Minmei

662
00:36:05,963 --> 00:36:08,332
Because I was jealous of Matilda...

663
00:36:08,399 --> 00:36:09,267
Not only

664
00:36:11,736 --> 00:36:13,271
you guys...

665
00:36:14,272 --> 00:36:16,774
Because I thought it was nice

666
00:36:18,142 --> 00:36:22,647
I became a second year junior high school student and became obsessed with stupid things.

667
00:36:23,581 --> 00:36:26,984
Yuta is so serious that it makes you laugh.

668
00:36:28,119 --> 00:36:30,655
I practiced too much and broke my elbow.

669
00:36:31,822 --> 00:36:35,693
I thought he was depressed because he couldn't play baseball anymore.

670
00:36:36,394 --> 00:36:38,262
I joined Eiken.

671
00:36:38,329 --> 00:36:40,998
Next time I'll stay up all night studying movies!

672
00:36:40,998 --> 00:36:41,732
This time I stayed up all night studying movies.

673
00:36:42,333 --> 00:36:43,467
Come on!

674
00:36:43,534 --> 00:36:47,305
(Akuri) Became a great otaku in no time.

675
00:36:49,040 --> 00:36:50,308
with strange guys

676
00:36:51,309 --> 00:36:53,044
I'm making a weird movie

677
00:36:54,178 --> 00:36:55,580
What is a man?

678
00:36:56,113 --> 00:37:00,685
I thought it was a good idea to be stupid.

679
00:37:02,119 --> 00:37:04,388
What happened to you earlier...

680
00:37:08,025 --> 00:37:09,460
I was happy for a while

681
00:37:11,596 --> 00:37:13,564
It's Yuta after all

682
00:37:16,767 --> 00:37:17,868
you

683
00:37:18,502 --> 00:37:22,239
stubborn and obstinate

684
00:37:24,041 --> 00:37:25,476
Fucking serious

685
00:37:26,477 --> 00:37:28,613
Always working hard

686
00:37:29,480 --> 00:37:30,648
Same way now

687
00:37:32,049 --> 00:37:33,050
that's why…

688
00:37:35,286 --> 00:37:37,054
Yuta is okay

689
00:37:37,955 --> 00:37:38,789
Yeah

690
00:37:38,856 --> 00:37:40,391
Don't get bored!

691
00:37:41,926 --> 00:37:44,862
Those who lead the way have a duty.

692
00:37:45,796 --> 00:37:49,300
There are people who have worked hard to watch your back.

693
00:37:50,001 --> 00:37:51,802
Don't let it end on its own

694
00:37:54,171 --> 00:37:56,340
Stay cool until the end!

695
00:37:59,677 --> 00:38:02,113
It's wonderful! Minmei-san!

696
00:38:03,648 --> 00:38:06,584
Yeah... ah... who are you?

697
00:38:07,752 --> 00:38:09,020
Someone's daughter?

698
00:38:09,086 --> 00:38:11,055
- (Kisuke) No... - (Hakuba) No, it's not.

699
00:38:11,122 --> 00:38:16,027
...It's a relationship that's difficult to explain...

700
00:38:16,527 --> 00:38:18,829
Ah! It's not about being a dad!

701
00:38:18,896 --> 00:38:21,499
Um... Ah, something about Mr. Chen.

702
00:38:21,565 --> 00:38:24,268
They said something like ``Paradise Lost.''

703
00:38:24,335 --> 00:38:27,171
I thought it would be bad if I let the old men go alone.

704
00:38:27,238 --> 00:38:28,072
I said that...

705
00:38:28,139 --> 00:38:30,174
- (Kisuke) Said... - (Hakuba) I'm the leader.

706
00:38:30,241 --> 00:38:31,242
Huh...

707
00:38:32,910 --> 00:38:37,348
Come to think of it, I've thought about it several times.

708
00:38:39,116 --> 00:38:41,485
If only I could talk to Matilda

709
00:38:42,987 --> 00:38:45,156
Life could have been different

710
00:38:49,860 --> 00:38:54,398
Find me the one who killed Matilda.

711
00:38:57,034 --> 00:38:58,169
Yeah

712
00:39:12,149 --> 00:39:14,552
(Yuta) Chen dropped this for me.

713
00:39:17,588 --> 00:39:18,522
Akari

714
00:39:19,724 --> 00:39:25,229
Stop calling yourself an old woman or an old woman.

715
00:39:27,098 --> 00:39:28,532
for us

716
00:39:30,601 --> 00:39:34,371
you are now and then

717
00:39:35,473 --> 00:39:37,641
Because I'll be Minmei forever

718
00:39:37,708 --> 00:39:41,078
‪♪～

719
00:39:59,563 --> 00:40:02,466
(Kisuke) Oh oh oh... Are you Minmei?

720
00:40:02,533 --> 00:40:05,536
(Hajime) She's as good as the rumors say, so let's have her come with us!

721
00:40:05,603 --> 00:40:07,271
(Akuri) Let go of me, you rude person!

722
00:40:07,338 --> 00:40:09,006
(Hajime/Kisuke) Come on!

723
00:40:09,073 --> 00:40:10,975
-(Akari) Let go! -(Yuta) Hey! Hey!

724
00:40:11,041 --> 00:40:12,910
Get your hands off that person!

725
00:40:13,644 --> 00:40:14,645
Huh?

726
00:40:15,212 --> 00:40:16,280
(Kisuke) It hurts, it hurts, it hurts, it hurts

727
00:40:16,347 --> 00:40:18,048
(Hajime) Cut cut! It's different from the script!

728
00:40:18,115 --> 00:40:19,717
Fufufufufu

729
00:40:19,784 --> 00:40:22,653
(Uncensored) It's not interesting, it's a time when heroines fight too.

730
00:40:22,720 --> 00:40:24,722
Nausicaa is the evolved form of Clarice.

731
00:40:24,789 --> 00:40:27,324
But it's different from the script I wrote!

732
00:40:27,391 --> 00:40:29,260
(Undistributed) Yes, it's fine, let's continue!

733
00:40:29,326 --> 00:40:31,162
-(Akari) Wow! -(Hajime) Wow!

734
00:40:31,228 --> 00:40:32,096
Huh

735
00:40:32,163 --> 00:40:34,865
(Unsold) Good, good! Minmei, defeat him!

736
00:40:34,932 --> 00:40:35,766
Beat it!

737
00:40:35,833 --> 00:40:38,135
(Hajime) Please help me without looking...

738
00:40:41,438 --> 00:40:43,007
(Misan) Hey, hey, don't lose!

739
00:40:53,784 --> 00:40:57,721
I also want to meet Matilda.

740
00:41:02,059 --> 00:41:04,361
-(Hajime) Oh, that! -(Kisuke) Oh~ I remember it!

741
00:41:04,428 --> 00:41:06,330
-(Kisuke) Yun, did you have it? -(Yuta) Oh

742
00:41:06,397 --> 00:41:08,899
Did you know? There's something like this on the back

743
00:41:08,966 --> 00:41:11,168
(Kisuke) Oooh, Ton-chan!

744
00:41:11,235 --> 00:41:12,069
(Hakuba) Tonchan?

745
00:41:12,136 --> 00:41:13,804
Matilda original character

746
00:41:13,871 --> 00:41:14,705
Huh?

747
00:41:14,772 --> 00:41:17,975
“Keep your head up and do your best!”…

748
00:41:21,979 --> 00:41:23,647
I remembered

749
00:41:23,714 --> 00:41:25,449
Why did you join EIKEN?

750
00:41:26,016 --> 00:41:28,152
Do you hate being called an otaku?

751
00:41:29,954 --> 00:41:31,489
That's uncool, that kind of thing

752
00:41:32,256 --> 00:41:33,524
Even if you make fun of me

753
00:41:33,591 --> 00:41:37,962
Even if I'm embarrassed, even if I'm hurt and covered in mud

754
00:41:38,028 --> 00:41:40,531
Live with a calm face and look forward

755
00:41:40,598 --> 00:41:42,766
Isn't that kind of person cool?

756
00:41:43,467 --> 00:41:47,271
(Hakuba) Memories are memories, not facts.

757
00:41:48,205 --> 00:41:52,076
Everyone wraps it up in their own way and turns it into a story.

758
00:41:52,142 --> 00:41:58,582
(Cell phone vibrating sound) ～♪

759
00:42:01,952 --> 00:42:02,953
(Hajime) Huh?

760
00:42:03,921 --> 00:42:04,922
Yeah

761
00:42:08,859 --> 00:42:09,860
hello

762
00:42:11,395 --> 00:42:15,499
(Akuri) I… I remembered.

763
00:42:16,200 --> 00:42:19,570
I saw it

764
00:42:20,571 --> 00:42:21,405
(Not scattered) Kya!

765
00:43:02,012 --> 00:43:04,214
(Hakuba) When the veil is lifted

766
00:43:04,281 --> 00:43:08,352
Can we really see it directly?

767
00:43:11,622 --> 00:43:12,623
(unlock sound)

768
00:43:24,501 --> 00:43:28,172
I'm sorry for being unnecessary.

769
00:43:32,209 --> 00:43:36,780
But I still can't help but do something

770
00:43:38,716 --> 00:43:42,219
If you guys continue to have trouble

771
00:43:43,087 --> 00:43:46,156
I'll do everything I can

772
00:43:47,691 --> 00:43:51,628
Again... I might be wrong though.

773
00:43:53,297 --> 00:43:54,765
I'll do what I can

774
00:43:59,436 --> 00:44:01,138
let me apologize too

775
00:44:05,109 --> 00:44:07,144
I'm really sorry but...

776
00:44:12,416 --> 00:44:13,650
Let's divorce

777
00:44:15,486 --> 00:44:19,923
 (Hakuba) Is there hope beyond that?
